description.zh-cn: 中华人民共和国吉林省的省会、副省级市。别称“北国春城”，曾作为满洲国首都“新京”。是中国重要的工业基地、最早的汽车工业和电影工业基地。
description.en: The capital and a sub-provincial city of Jilin Province, People's Republic of China. Known as the 'Spring City of Northland', it once served as 'Hsinking', the capital of Manchukuo. It is a major industrial base in China, and the earliest center for the automotive and film industries in the country.

description.zh-cn: 中华人民共和国的省级行政区，省会长春市。
description.en: A province of the People's Republic of China, with Changchun as its capital.

description.zh-cn: 1932年至1945年间由大日本帝国在中国东北地区扶植的傀儡政权，首都是新京（今长春）。
description.en: A puppet state of the Empire of Japan in Northeast China from 1932 to 1945, with its capital at Hsinking (present-day Changchun).

description.zh-cn: 中国政治人物，现任中国共产党长春市委员会书记。
description.en: A Chinese politician, currently serving as the Communist Party Secretary of Changchun.

nodes.id: 中国共产党长春市委员会

zh-cn: 中国共产党长春市委员会
en: Changchun Municipal Committee of the Communist Party of China

description.zh-cn: 中国共产党在长春市的领导机关。
description.en: The leading organ of the Communist Party of China in Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 中国政治人物，现任长春市人民代表大会常务委员会主任。
description.en: A Chinese politician, currently serving as the Chairman of the Standing Committee of the Changchun Municipal People's Congress.

nodes.id: 长春市人民代表大会常务委员会

zh-cn: 长春市人民代表大会常务委员会
en: Standing Committee of the Changchun Municipal People's Congress

description.zh-cn: 长春市的国家权力机关。
description.en: The organ of state power in Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 中国政治人物，现任长春市人民政府市长。
description.en: A Chinese politician, currently serving as the Mayor of the Changchun Municipal People's Government.

description.zh-cn: 长春市的行政机关。
description.en: The administrative organ of Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 中国政治人物，现任中国人民政治协商会议长春市委员会主席。
description.en: A Chinese politician, currently serving as the Chairman of the Changchun Municipal Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference.

nodes.id: 中国人民政治协商会议长春市委员会

zh-cn: 中国人民政治协商会议长春市委员会
en: Changchun Municipal Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference

description.zh-cn: 中国人民政治协商会议在长春市的地方组织。
description.en: The local organization of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference in Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 清朝第七位皇帝，批准设立长春厅。
description.en: The seventh emperor of the Qing dynasty, who approved the establishment of Changchun Ting.

description.zh-cn: 清代在长春地区设立的行政机构，隶属于吉林将军，后改为长春府。
description.en: An administrative division established in the Changchun area during the Qing dynasty, subordinate to the General of Jilin, later upgraded to Changchun Fu.

description.zh-cn: 清代东北地区的军事和行政长官。
description.en: A military and administrative governor in Northeast China during the Qing dynasty.

description.zh-cn: 日本关东军在中国东北蓄意制造并发动的一场侵华战争，是日本帝国主义侵华的开端。事变后第二天，日本即占领长春。
description.en: An invasion of Manchuria staged by Japanese troops, which marked the beginning of the Japanese invasion of China. Japan occupied Changchun the day after the incident.

description.zh-cn: 东亚国家。在九一八事变后占领长春，并扶植满洲国。
description.en: An East Asian country. It occupied Changchun after the Mukden Incident and established the puppet state of Manchukuo.

description.zh-cn: 满洲国时期长春的行政建制，由满洲国国务院直辖。
description.en: The administrative status of Changchun during the Manchukuo period, directly administered by the State Council of Manchukuo.

description.zh-cn: 满洲国的中央行政机关。
description.en: The central administrative organ of Manchukuo.

description.zh-cn: 苏联的武装力量。1945年8月攻入满洲国并占领新京。
description.en: The armed forces of the Soviet Union. In August 1945, they invaded Manchukuo and occupied Hsinking.

description.zh-cn: 第二次国共内战时期中国共产党在中国东北地区建立的武装力量，是中国人民解放军第四野战军的前身。
description.en: The armed forces established by the Communist Party of China in Northeast China during the second Chinese Civil War, the predecessor of the Fourth Field Army of the PLA.

description.zh-cn: 中国军事将领，曾指挥东北民主联军发起围攻长春战役。
description.en: A Chinese military general who commanded the Northeast Democratic United Army in the offensive on Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 1946年由东北民主联军发起的针对长春的军事行动。
description.en: A military operation against Changchun launched by the Northeast Democratic United Army in 1946.

description.zh-cn: 1948年国共内战期间，由东北野战军对国民党军守卫的长春进行的围困战。
description.en: A military siege of Changchun, defended by Kuomintang forces, conducted by the Northeast Field Army during the Chinese Civil War in 1948.

description.zh-cn: 中国人民解放军在第二次国共内战时期的主力部队之一，由东北民主联军改称而来。
description.en: One of the main forces of the People's Liberation Army during the second Chinese Civil War, renamed from the Northeast Democratic United Army.

description.zh-cn: 中国军事将领，曾指挥东北野战军包围长春，发起长春围困战。
description.en: A Chinese military general who commanded the Northeast Field Army to besiege Changchun, initiating the Siege of Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 中华人民共和国的武装力量。
description.en: The armed forces of the People's Republic of China.

nodes.id: 长春市 (中华人民共和国直辖市)

zh-cn: 长春市 (中华人民共和国直辖市)

description.zh-cn: 1953年至1954年间长春市作为中央直辖市的行政建制。
description.en: The administrative status of Changchun as a centrally-administered municipality from 1953 to 1954.

description.zh-cn: 中华人民共和国成立初期东北大行政区的最高行政管理机关。
description.en: The highest administrative body of the Northeast Great Administrative Region in the early days of the People's Republic of China.

description.zh-cn: 中华人民共和国成立初期的最高国家权力机关。
description.en: The supreme organ of state power in the early days of the People's Republic of China.

description.zh-cn: 吉林省的行政机关。
description.en: The administrative organ of Jilin Province.

description.zh-cn: 吉林省下辖的地级市，曾为吉林省省会。
description.en: A prefecture-level city in Jilin Province, formerly the provincial capital.

description.zh-cn: 吉林省辖县级市，由长春市代管。
description.en: A county-level city in Jilin Province, administered by Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 吉林省下辖的地级市，曾代管公主岭市。
description.en: A prefecture-level city in Jilin Province, which formerly administered Gongzhuling.

nodes.id: 中华人民共和国国务院

zh-cn: 中华人民共和国国务院
en: State Council of the People's Republic of China

description.zh-cn: 中华人民共和国的最高国家行政机关。
description.en: The chief administrative authority of the People's Republic of China.

description.zh-cn: 日本宫城县的首府，长春市的友好城市。
description.en: The capital city of Miyagi Prefecture, Japan, and a sister city of Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 塞尔维亚第二大城市，长春市的友好城市。
description.en: The second largest city in Serbia, and a sister city of Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 英国英格兰的城市，长春市的友好城市。
description.en: A city in England, United Kingdom, and a sister city of Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 德国下萨克森州的城市，长春市的友好城市。
description.en: A city in Lower Saxony, Germany, and a sister city of Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 长春市是吉林省的省会。
description.en: Changchun is the capital of Jilin Province.

relationships.target: 中国共产党长春市委员会
长春市人民代表大会常务委员会
中国人民政治协商会议长春市委员会

description.zh-cn: 嘉庆帝发布上谕，同意设立长春厅作为官方行政机构。
description.en: The Jiaqing Emperor issued an imperial edict approving the establishment of Changchun Ting as an official administrative body.

description.zh-cn: 长春厅隶属于吉林将军管辖。
description.en: Changchun Ting was under the jurisdiction of the General of Jilin.

description.zh-cn: 九一八事变是日本侵华的开端，事变后日本占领了长春。
description.en: The Mukden Incident marked the beginning of Japan's invasion of China, after which Japan occupied Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 满洲国定都长春，并将其更名为“新京”，作为其政治、军事、经济和文化中心。
description.en: Manchukuo established its capital in Changchun, renaming it 'Hsinking' to serve as its political, military, economic, and cultural center.

description.zh-cn: 新京特别市由满洲国国务院直辖。
description.en: The Hsinking Special Municipality was directly administered by the State Council of Manchukuo.

description.zh-cn: 1945年8月，苏联红军攻入满洲国，导致其灭亡。
description.en: In August 1945, the Soviet Red Army invaded Manchukuo, leading to its collapse.

description.zh-cn: 东北民主联军发起围攻长春的战役，并短暂占领该市。
description.en: The Northeast Democratic United Army launched an offensive on Changchun and briefly occupied the city.

description.zh-cn: 周保中指挥东北民主联军吉林军区部队发起围攻长春战役。
description.en: Zhou Baozhong commanded the Jilin Military Region troops of the Northeast Democratic United Army to launch the offensive on Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 东北野战军包围长春，发起了长春围困战，并最终占领该城。
description.en: The Northeast Field Army besieged Changchun, initiating the Siege of Changchun, and eventually captured the city.

description.zh-cn: 东北野战军萧劲光部包围长春，发起长春围困战。
description.en: Troops under the command of Xiao Jinguang from the Northeast Field Army besieged Changchun, initiating the Siege of Changchun.

relationships.source: 长春市 (中华人民共和国直辖市)

description.zh-cn: 长春市作为中央直辖市期间，由东北行政委员会代理管辖。
description.en: During its time as a centrally-administered municipality, Changchun was governed by the Northeast Administrative Committee.

relationships.target: 长春市 (中华人民共和国直辖市)

description.zh-cn: 中央人民政府委员会通过决定，撤销大区一级行政机构，长春市的中央直辖市地位被撤销，改为省辖市。
description.en: The Central People's Government Committee passed a resolution to abolish the great administrative regions, revoking Changchun's status as a centrally-administered municipality and making it a provincially-administered city.

description.zh-cn: 吉林省人民政府从吉林市迁至长春市，长春市自此成为吉林省省会。
description.en: The Jilin Provincial People's Government relocated from Jilin City to Changchun, making Changchun the provincial capital.

relationships.source: 中华人民共和国国务院

description.zh-cn: 国务院批复同意将原由四平市代管的公主岭市划归长春市代管。
description.en: The State Council approved the transfer of the administration of Gongzhuling from Siping to Changchun.

description.zh-cn: 长春市与日本仙台市建立友好城市关系。
description.en: Changchun established a sister city relationship with Sendai, Japan.

description.zh-cn: 长春市与塞尔维亚诺维萨德市建立友好城市关系。
description.en: Changchun established a sister city relationship with Novi Sad, Serbia.

description.zh-cn: 长春市与英国伯明翰市建立友好城市关系。
description.en: Changchun established a sister city relationship with Birmingham, UK.

description.zh-cn: 长春市与德国沃尔夫斯堡市建立友好城市关系。
description.en: Changchun established a sister city relationship with Wolfsburg, Germany.
